arts.ttl: Leyton Orient denied FA Cup upset by Manchester City
arts.sum: Jamie Donley’s first-half wonder strike from just a few yards inside the City half gave Richie Wellens’ side the lead after 16 minutes, with the goal ultimately going down as an own goal by visiting keeper Stefan Ortega. "I’m just a little bit disappointed today that we didn’t have the players available.

arts.ttl: Charlie Kelman’s late goal secures Leyton Orient victory over Lincoln
